title: Biden holds historic international summit at Camp David
description: President Biden hosted an international summit at Camp David, bringing together Japan and South Korea who are facing common risks from North Korea’s nuclear provocations and China’s more aggressive show of military strength in the region. NBC News’ Kelly O’Donnell reports.

title: U.K. nurse found guilty of multiple baby murders
description: Lucy Letby has been found guilty of killing seven babies and attacking six others while working at the Countess of Chester Hospital in northwest England, as Sky News’ Katerina Vittozzi reports.

title: Biden strengthens U.S. ties with Japan and South Korea as leaders meet at Camp David
description: The trilateral summit comes as tensions between the U.S. and China have risen in recent years over Taiwan, economic issues and a spy balloon.

title: Rep. Ocasio-Cortez calls on U.S. to declassify documents on Chile’s 1973 coup
description: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez said Thursday in Chile that it was imperative for the United States to declassify documents that could shed light on Washington’s involvement in the South American country’s 1973 coup.

title: Iran arrests female activists in crackdown ahead of protests anniversary
description: Iran has detained women's rights activists in a crackdown ahead of the anniversary of the Mahsa Amini protests.

title: Neonatal nurse who wrote she was 'evil' found guilty of murdering babies
description: Lucy Letby, a British nurse who wrote a note describing herself as “evil,” was found guilty of murdering 7 babies and attempting to kill 6 others.

title: Moscow says its air defenses shot down a Ukrainian drone over the city
description: Russian air defenses shot down a Ukrainian drone over central Moscow early Friday and some fragments fell on an exposition center, officials said. Surveillance video captured the flash and sound of at least one explosion.

title: Drone attack on Moscow damages building and disrupts air traffic
description: A Ukrainian drone smashed into a building in central Moscow on Friday after Russian air defenses shot it down, disrupting air traffic at all the civilian airports of the Russian capital, Russian officials said.

title: Biden hosts trilateral summit with Japan and South Korea
description: President Biden is hosting the leaders of Japan and South Korea at Camp David in the first trilateral meeting between the three nations amid growing regional tensions with North Korea. NBC News’ Kristen Welker and Janis Mackey Frayer have the details.

title: Firefighters battle to control worst wildfire in decades on Spanish island of Tenerife
description: Firefighters battled overnight to try to bring under control the worst wildfire in decades on the Spanish Canary Island of Tenerife, a major tourist destination, officials said Friday.

title: North Koreans face increasing repression and threat of starvation, U.N. says
description: North Korea is increasing its repression of human rights and there are reports of starvation as the economic situation worsens, the U.N. rights chief said.

title: Thousands order to leave as Canadian firefighters battle wildfires
description: Canadian fire crews battled to prevent wildfires from reaching the northern city of Yellowknife, where all 20,000 residents are leaving by car and plane after an evacuation order was declared.

title: China’s Xi calls for measures to mitigate disastrous flooding amid economic slowdown
description: Chinese leader Xi Jinping has called for measures to mitigate the effects of this year’s disastrous flooding which has left scores dead and inflicted massive damage on crops, homes and infrastructure

title: Out-of-control wildfire scorches Spain’s Tenerife island, affecting thousands
description: An out-of-control wildfire on the Spanish Canary island of Tenerife has burned thousands of acres and affected nearly 8,000 people who are either evacuated or confined, authorities said Thursday.

title: Private jet crashes onto a highway, killing 8 on board and 2 on the ground
description: At least 10 people were killed after a small private jet crashed on the highway Thursday in the suburbs of Malaysia’s capital, officials said.

title: Passenger jet crash onto highway kills 10 in Malaysia
description: 10 people were killed Thursday when a small plane lost control and crashed onto a highway as it was heading to Subang airport in Malaysia.

title: Residents of Canada's Northwest Territories race to flee capital as wildfire nears
description: Residents in the capital of Canada’s Northwest Territories were rushing to beat a noon Friday deadline to evacuate their homes as one of hundreds of wildfires raging in the territories moved closer to the city of 20,000.

title: Chinese property giant Evergrande files for bankruptcy protection in U.S. court
description: China’s heavily indebted property developer Evergrande on Thursday filed for Chapter 15 bankruptcy protection in a U.S. court.

title: Pilot dies after mid-flight medical emergency, officials say
description: A veteran pilot for a Chilean airline died after a mid-flight medical emergency, the airline said.

title: American citizen charged with espionage in Russia
description: U.S. citizen Gene Spector has been charged with espionage in Russia, according to Russian state media. Spector was convicted in a Russian court last year on a bribery charge.
